'''St. Patrick Academy''' is a [[private school|private]], [[Roman Catholic]], coeducational [[high school]] in [[Providence, Rhode Island]].  It is located in the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Providence]].

==Background==
Originally established as an all-boy school in 1843, St. Patrick Academy was reestablished as a high school in 2009 after closing the associated elementary school grades 1-5.  The original high school was first established in 1933 and closed in 1970.<ref name="A 'miracle' school rises again">{{cite web|url=http://stpatrickacademyri.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Providence-Journal-Miracle-School-December-15-2011.pdf|title=A 'miracle' school rises again|date=2011-12-15|accessdate=2015-09-15|author=Richard C. Dujardin|publisher=Providence Journal}}</ref>  It is the oldest Catholic school in Rhode Island.<ref name="School History">{{cite web|url=http://stpatrickacademyri.com/about-us/school-history|title=School History|accessdate=2015-09-15|author=SPA|publisher=St. Patrick Academy}}</ref>

